# pro-simulation

This folder contains the simulation code for the PRO–PFS project.

## Structure (in order of use)

pro-simulation/
│
├── parameters.R                   # Calculation of parameters β1 and β3 for PRO model (different for TIME scenarios: BEFORE, AT, AFTER)
│
├── scenario_table.rds             # Parameters output. A table with β1 and β3 parameters for each scenario to be used in DGM.
│
├── dgm.R                          # Data-generating mechanism
│   ├── pro_generator              # - generator for expected PRO at time t (linear)
│   ├── compute_PD                 # - generator of PD (exp) and convertion to the nearest visit week
│   ├── compute_PRO_event          # - PRO event detection
│   ├── collection_scenarios       # - definition of COLLECTION scenarios
│   ├── simulate                   # - simulation function (PRO at baseline, PRO at each week + correlated errors, PD events)
│   ├── sim_out                    # - running 200 simulations for each TIME scenario
│
├── simulated_pro_datasets.rds     # DM output. A list of 3 TIME scenarios (BEFORE, AT, AFTER),
│                                  # each with 200 replication, each with 3 COLLECTION scenarios (full, stop, reduced)
│                                  # Variables: patient, arm, PRO_status, PRO_event_week, PD_status, PD_event_week, collection
│
├── analysis.R                     # Analysis of simulated datasets. Analysis models:
│   ├── run_cox                    # - Cox PH
│   ├── run_rr                     # - Poisson log-link
│   ├── analysis_results           # - creation of an output table
│
├── analysis_results.rds           # Analysis output. A table with 1,800 entries (3 TIME scenarios x 200 simulations x 3 COLLECTION scenarios)
│                                  # - hazard ratios and median time to deterioration
│                                  # - relative risk at weeks 27, 36, 54
│
├── performance.R                  # Performance measures of the analysis outputs. Summary accross all scenarios.
│                                  # - geometric HR mean
│                                  # - HR distribution (95% percentile interval)
│                                  # - mean of median deterioration times for control and treatment
│                                  # - plot for geometric HR mean with 2.5–97.5% percentile interval
│                                  # - bias of HR means between reduced/stop and full scenarios (+plot)
│                                  # - geometric RR means for weeks 27,36,54
│                                  # - RR distribution (95% percentile interval)
│                                  # - plot for geometric RR mean with 2.5–97.5% percentile interval
│                                  # - bias of RR means between reduced/stop and full scenarios (+plot)
│
├── checks/                        # Validity checks for the code
│   ├── calibrate.betas.R          # Script to calibrate β1 AND β3 with a small number of simulations if beta5 is itroduced
│   ├── calibrated_scenario_table_beta5=(-0.1) # Parameters output. A table with β1 and β3 parameters for each scenario when beta5 = -0.1.
│   ├── calibrated_scenario_table_beta5=(-1) # Parameters output. A table with β1 and β3 parameters for each scenario when beta5 = -1.
│   ├── dgm_copula/                # Alternative DGM where PFS and PRO at baseline are simulated using Copula and correlated (+ analysis and performance check)
│   ├── dgm_with_beta5/            # Alternative DGM with beta 5 (PD indicator) in PRO model. If PD happened, the slope changes (+ analysis and performance check)
│   ├── event_check/               # Calculation of N of events for specific scenarios
│   ├── fixed_PD_check/            # Alternative DGM (first tried) where PFS is not simulated and PD events are fixed at weeks 36/54 for all patients (+ analysis and performance check)
│   ├── km_curves.R                # KM curves for PRO and PD for one replication in one scenario
│   ├── pro_trajectory/            # Plot for individual PRO trajectories for 1 scenario (the dataset is taken from the simulate() function)
│   ├── uncertainty                # Comparison of 2 ways to extract CIs: empirical and from Cox PH model
│
└── README                         # Explanation of project flow


